 O God! My heart doth sing Thy praise.
O God! Thou art my God alone;
O God! My heart doth sing Thy praise;
In darkest night, in brightest dawn,
Thy presence fills my soul's deep ways.

Thy love, a flame that burns so bright,
Guides me through life's plodding, weary flight;
Through trials and through tribulations' test,
Thou holdest me, and I am blessed.

In Thy great mercy, I am free;
My heart, a vessel, Thou dost fill with glee;
The world, with all its noise and strife,
Fades into silence, and I find my life.

O God! Thou art my Rock, my Shore;
My Refuge, where I am forever more;
In Thee, I find my peaceful nest;
My soul, a bird, that finds its rest.

Thy Word, a lamp that shines so bright,
Lights up the path, and makes my heart take flight;
Thy Spirit, a gentle breeze that blows,
And in its whisper, my heart overflows.

O God! Thou art my God alone;
O God! My heart doth sing Thy praise;
Forever and forever, I will adore,
And in Thy love, my soul will soar.  #poetry #prayer #worship
